Cloud environments should be reviewed regularly to improve security, performance, reliability, and cost efficiency.

Continuous improvement activities include:

* Reviewing monitoring data
* Evaluating security recommendations
* Optimizing resource utilization
* Updating documentation
* Automating repetitive tasks
* Implementing lessons learned from incidents

For example, recurring CPU alerts may reveal the need for application optimization instead of simply increasing virtual machine size.

A real-life use case is IT teams conducting monthly operational reviews to identify improvement opportunities.

Continuous improvement ensures cloud environments remain efficient as business requirements evolve.
